sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ElChu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Takes in a PoPS signal, and expresses a SMTa Metallothionein copper sequestering protein
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Dan Nelsen, Shivani Torres, Aaron Goebel
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: THe SMTa gene comes from e.Coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We made some modifications to the genetic code to delete repeated sequences. We also manually inputed a termination sequence prior to the Transcription Terminator as a secondary terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J119025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BD2 bicistronic translational junction - Lowest efficiency
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The BD2 bicistronic translational junction was engineered by Vivek Mutalik and The BIOFAB Team at biofab.org. It includes an RBS that allows translation of a leader polypeptide. The leader has a second RBS embedded in it. The stop codon for the leader polypeptide overlaps with the start codon for the gene of interest.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vivek Mutalik
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The bicistronic translational junction was designed by Team Leader Vivek Mutalik at BioFAB. It is is intended to give reproducible and consistent expression for various genes of interest.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K174008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: SmtA metallothionein protein with CotC and Gfp fusion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Metallothionein protein can bind to heavy metals such as cadmium, arsenic, mercury, silver. By fusing CotC spore coat protein from ''Bacillus subtilis'', it can be localized to the spore coat, hence trap the metals into bacterial spores. It is also fused with Gfp to see the spores with the proteins using a microscope.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: The Newcastle 2009 iGEM team
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: smtA sequence is taken from ''E. coli''
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It is integrated to ''B. subtilis'' using the homology between cotC fusion and the native copy of cotC on the chromosome.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
